==English==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|yerling}}, {{m|enm|yerlyng}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|year|ling}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|jaarling|t=yearling}}, {{cog|de|Jährling|t=yearling}}.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# An [[animal]] that is between one and two [[year]]s old; one that is in its second year (but not yet two full years old).
#: {{ux|en|a '''yearling''' lamb}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Henry Fountain|title=‘The Worst Thing I Can Ever Remember’: How Drought Is Crushing Ranchers|work=The New York Times|date=2021-08-25|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/25/climate/drought-cattle.html|issn=0362-4331|author2=Benjamin Rasmussen|passage=Tom Fettig and his wife, Kim, were there with 60 '''yearlings''', about half of a herd they were helping their son raise on the outskirts of Bismarck.}}
# A [[racehorse]] that is [[considered]] to be one year old until a [[subsequent]] [[January]] 1st.<!-- I think -->
# {{lb|en|US}} A [[sophomore]] at [[West Point]] [[military]] [[academy]].
#* '''1910''', H. Irving Hancock, ''Dick Prescott's Second Year at West Point'' (page 84)
#*: "But is a [[plebe]] forbidden to stroll here?"<br>"If a plebe did have the brass to try it," replied Anstey slowly, "I reckon he would have to fight the whole '''yearling''' class in turn."
